        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 10 at 9:17PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 917 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 17 miles east of Broadus to 22 miles
west of Alzada, or extending from 17 miles east of Broadus to 38
miles southeast of Broadus, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Alzada, Hammond, Boyes and Ridge.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
